<br>
As a slight modification, I say make your pet 100% (or more) hasted, big AC, resists, HP, etc boosts, and make the duration based on your amount of mana (Like wizzies manaburn is based on amount of mana they have).  Rhasin said to make it a mana DoT, but I don't think that should be done.  Most of us have seen the posts about how with rods and a personal healer, you could have infinite mana, so conceivably with a mana DoT you could keep it going forever if you were quick enough.  Just make it drain all your mana in one shot, and have its duration based on that amount of mana (shouldn't be THAT hard to code.  Just make duration based on mana instead of fixed amount.  The were able to extend duration with focus, so there IS code to modify duration already in there).<br>
<br>
This is one of the better ideas i've seen on how to make us have a good damage role in raids.  We'll still be rodding before and after this ability, but it makes us useful as more than just mana hand-off, and will make magicians more desireable on raids for the damage caused.<br>
 <p>Eriol Telcontar - Dragons Revolt<BR>
Magician of the 39th Summoning<BR>
