<br>
Thanks for updating me on what I'm doing, and letting me know what I should be doing. Phew, I can rest easy now! Here was me running around on autopilot all this time!<br>
<br>
In case you missed it btw, the reason I added the rather savage negative side-affects is that an additional 70-100 DPS over a 5 minute period is 21,000 - 30,000 points of damage. This was then umber I came up with as an acceptable use of mana during a long-term bossmob encounter compared with Trans-Rodding.<br>
<br>
However, it is a rather extreme damage per mana ratio. I rationalised that either the effect would not be made this good (and hence would be useless when compared against Trans Rodding) or it would have to have some reasonably serious side-affects.<br>
<br>
1k damage is not going to kill anyone, or drop anyone with half a care to what they are doing into frenzy range. I am in no way uber and I easily pop 3k hit points fuly raid buffed - dropping 1.75 bubs of life with a backup healer ready to help me is not going to kill me.<br>
<br>
Being stunned or silenced for a minute or so is not going to kill me either. After all, I just blew all my mana on this great Frenzied Burnout - what else am I going to do anyway? Melee? <p><B><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26251">Hogfather</A></b><P>
